    id: "ethics-amedex-0028",
    topic: "Ethics & Professionalism",
    subtopic: "Cervical cancer screening - LGBTQ+ health",
    stem: `A 26-year-old female comes for cervical cancer screening by HPV testing. She never had sexual activity with a man but is a lesbian and has a girlfriend. She prefers to see a lesbian-friendly healthcare provider for her test. Which of the following would be the most appropriate action in this situation?`,
